                    <div class="accordion-header">What educational background is needed for environmental engineering?</div>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>A bachelor's degree in Environmental Engineering, Civil Engineering, or a related field provides a good foundation. Knowledge in chemistry, biology, fluid mechanics, and earth sciences is valuable. Advanced roles in specialized areas or research may require a master's degree or PhD. Professional certification like Environmental Engineer (EVP) can enhance career prospects.</p>
